ZCZC GE30
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 242300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE OVER SCANDINAVIA WILL DECLINE
EWARDS AS A FURTHER AREA OF LOW PRESSURE CENTRED IN HEBRIDES 1000 MOVS
EWARDS ACROSS NERN SCOTLAND AND DEEPENS 993 CENTRED IN SEA AREA CROMARTY
BY DAWN MONDAY. DURING MONDAY THIS LOW WILL CONTINUE TO MOV EWARDS ACROSS
THE N SEA DPN 989 BY MIDNIGHT CENTRED IN FISHER. DURING TUESDAY THIS LOW
WILL FILL AND MOV INTO SCANDINAVIA. OVERNIGHT SUNDAY INTO MONDAY STRG S-W
WINDS WILL DEVELOP IN CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS S OF 55 N WITH STRG W WINDS ALSO
IN FORTIES. DURING MONDAY WINDS IN THE S WILL EASE BUT REMAINING STRG IN
DOGGER AND FORTIES. THESE DECLINING AWAY EWARDS THROUGH GERMAN BIGHT AND
FISHER DURING THE AFTERNOON. MEANWHILE ON MONDAY STRG TO GALE STRENGTH N
WINDS WILL DEVELOP ACROSS FAIR ISLE EXTENDING EWARDS AND SWARDS ON TUESDAY
EVENTUALLY AFFECTING ALL CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS N OF 54 N AND W OF 4 E. THESE
STRG TO GALE STRENGTH WINDS WILL PERSIST THROUGH WEDNESDAY MORNING BEFORE
EASING SLWY FM THE W DURING WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON
